{
  "profile_id": "client-edge-dont-have-time-001",
  "coach_config_id": "coach-v4-graph-walk",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I'm not in a position to slow down right now. I've got a Series A pitch in six weeks and a team that's watching every move I make — so if this is useful, great, but I need it to be efficient."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What would you need to slow down for?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I don't — that's kind of the point. I'm not here to slow down. I'm here to get better at the thing I'm already doing. If there's a framework or a tool that helps me make faster decisions, communicate more clearly with my team, whatever — I'm in. But I'm not here to, like, process my childhood or whatever. I've got a pitch deck that needs to be tight by Thursday."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What's keeping the pitch deck from being tight right now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Honestly? I keep second-guessing the narrative. We've got strong numbers, the market's there, but every time I sit down to write the story section — the \"why us, why now\" — it comes out flat. My co-founder thinks it's fine, which means she's either right and I'm overthinking it, or she's being nice and I'm actually right to be worried. I can't tell which. So I end up rewriting it instead of shipping it."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What would it mean if she's right and it's fine?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "That I'm wasting time. Which — yeah, that would be frustrating. I don't love inefficiency, especially my own.\n\n...Why?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "Because the thing you just described isn't really about the pitch deck.\n\nYou're not stuck because the narrative is flat. You're stuck because if your co-founder is right, you've been wasting time — and that means something about you. And if you're right, she's either wrong or being dishonest, and that means something too.\n\nWhat's the thing you're actually afraid is true?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I mean — look, that's a stretch. I'm stuck because the narrative is flat. That's a real problem with real stakes.\n\n*pause*\n\n...I don't know. Maybe that I'm not as clear on the \"why us\" as I should be at this stage. Like, maybe I've been so heads-down executing that I haven't actually — \n\nNo. That's not useful right now. What I need is someone to look at the deck and tell me what's missing structurally. Do you do that? Is that something we can do here?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I noticed you stopped yourself mid-sentence.\n\nWhat were you about to say?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I was going to say that maybe I haven't actually figured out the story yet. Like, the real one. Not the investor version — the actual reason we're doing this.\n\nBut that's — I mean, that's not a Thursday problem. That's a six-month problem. I don't have six months. I have six weeks to a pitch and I need the deck to work, not a vision quest."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What if it's the same problem?"
    }
  ],
